Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Input sequences of single-particle indices", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.887456256699031*^9, 3.887456258704954*^9}, {
  3.888315083848212*^9, 
  3.8883150934469776`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"449e637c-f7d0-4628-9d06-\
e4ea8c1dfce7"],

Cell["\<\
Loading of the 240 (120) input sequences of single particle indices, \
corresponding to left-and-right-dressed Feynman diagrams of disjoint direct \
type with a two-body vertex and two non-identical (identical) one-body \
interaction vertices. Contributions with non-identical vertices are twice the \
ones generated by two identical vertices, as the former do not possess any \
vertex permutation symmetry and hence have multiplicity corresponding to the \
one generated by internal single-particle index exchanges in the two-body \
vertex.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGAQA2IQ/fjUjej4H28cu54lJIDokiTzrB4gHaIeBabl+mOP
vGN463gpvhtMi53jV3kPpHW68sG0bn3GJzbOt44/ds4E03WizcyyCm8de+qf
